name: Red Poster 3 Yoda
desc: I had set off to the local marketplace early in the morning. Once I arrived, the usual hustle and bustle of the area had seemingly been replaced by lethargic, slow, and distracted patrons. Not terribly uncommon - on Coruscant you find many small-time celebrities who can bring most any area of the city to a standstill. Pushing my way through towards the clothing district, I was resolved not to be yet another blank-eyed fan. In my haste, I pushed with too much gusto. The resulting succession of tumbling bodies poured outward from me in all directions, knocking more than a few people off the causeway, towards their death below. In a blur of green, I felt something fly overhead. Before I realized it, those falling were saved. And then he looked at me and spoke one sentence  Hurry we must not. Muddled your mind becomes. A form of violence haste is. The dark side.

name: Clone Helmet (pedestal) 2 Cody
desc: Travelling through the cities of Kamino, I felt myself lost in a sea of familiarity. Aside from the striking appearance of the odd Kaminoan, it had become quite apparent I was standing amongst the next wave that will come to the defense of the Republic. They all looked identical, and I pondered how sad it was that though they may modify their look with a simple haircut or some other affectation, they still will don identical uniforms dedicated to destroying any semblance of identity they had created. But one had struck my eye. I watched him as he put on his helmet, and realized he had decorated it. The gold patches stood out boldly, and I smiled to myself. It would seem no two stories are as identical as I might think.

name: Counter Chair
desc: A chair with a low back perfect for a cafe counter.

name: Abstract Sculpture Bundle
desc: These post-modern abstract sculptures will add class to any room. This bundle contains  Abstract Sculpture Number One Abstract Sculpture Number Two Abstract Sculpture Number Three

name: Space Cube (1) - Glass - White
desc: The Space Cube (1), as in one compartment, is a great way to decorate your Space Apartment. Each Space Cube (1) set comes with the open, closed and glass versions of your color choice. Check out the awesome Space Cube (1) Bundle for more colorful stack em and mismatch em possibilities.

name: Seasonal Stockings
desc: Make sure they have something to hang on their wall this year.

name: Apocalyptic Brown Couch
desc: Salvaged and repaired from a destroyed military mess hall.

name: Valentines Day 2013 - Dinner Chair
desc: Love is in the air this Valentines Day. Get in the romantic spirit with this exclusive reward item.

name: BoxBeats Mini  Dance
desc: This stylish sound system comes jam packed with over 10 amazing dance tracks for you and your friends to listen to while you bust some moves. This active item also allows you to select specific tracks to play, set the volume and even randomise the track list. This is an essential item for your apartment. This item has the same music tracks as the original, but the object representing this item is 75% smaller in physical size. NB - There may be a delay when you place the item whilst the music tracks download.

name: Male Clothed Mannequin (1)
desc: The Jam Jar was established in the 1940 s as THE place to go. Discover the opulence and grandeur of this by gone era in a building rescued and restored to its rightful glory. Whether you decide to return it to its full boutique status, use its exquisite detail as a backdrop for a gallery or as the venue of the latest fashion event, The Jam Jar will still prove to be THE place to be seen.

name: Divine Display PODI Fireworks
desc: This box contains  Bombette Burst - A powerful green explosion Jet o Gold - A sustained fountain of sparkling gold Kissin the Sky - A cloud of tiny, delicate crosses Rising Horizon - Glaringly bright flash dogged by a plume of green smoke Ready-Steady-Go - Traffic lights in the sky Important  PODI Fireworks can only be used in conjuction with the Pyrotechnic Overhead Display Interface Active Object.

name: Valentines Gift
desc: This active item contains Valentine gifts for you and your friends. You can also gift ONE Sparkling Diamond Ring (male and female) to the friend of your choosing. Choose wisely.

name: Slave I Sofa

name: Snug Coffee Table

name: Clone Helmet (pedestal) 1 Rex
desc: Travelling through the cities of Kamino, I felt myself lost in a sea of familiarity. Aside from the striking appearance of the odd Kaminoan, it had become quite apparent I was standing amongst the next wave that will come to the defense of the Republic. They all looked identical, and I pondered how sad it was that though they may modify their look with a simple haircut or some other affectation, they still will don identical uniforms dedicated to destroying any semblance of identity they had created. But one had struck my eye. I watched him as he put on his helmet, and realized he had decorated it. The blue stripes stood out strongly, and I smiled to myself. It would seem no two stories are as identical as I might think.

The flowing sound of water produced enough white noise that I could let my mind drift, just a little bit. I thought of great space battles, smugglers defying the odds, and a young man raised on a farm who would become the hero of the Galaxy. After all, I was standing next to my new Yoda Water Fountain. How could I think of anything else?

name: Clone Helmet (pedestal) 3 Gree
desc: Travelling through the cities of Kamino, I felt myself lost in a sea of familiarity. Aside from the striking appearance of the odd Kaminoan, it had become quite apparent I was standing amongst the next wave that will come to the defense of the Republic. They all looked identical, and I pondered how sad it was that though they may modify their look with a simple haircut or some other affectation, they still will don identical uniforms dedicated to destroying any semblance of identity they had created. But one had struck my eye. I watched him as he put on his helmet, and realized he had decorated it. The deep green and silver was like nothing I had seen, and I smiled to myself. It would seem no two stories are as identical as I might think.
